Save: `CTRL + O` → Enter → `CTRL + X`

---

## 📜 3. Add License (Important)

👉 Go to GitHub while creating repo:
- Choose **MIT License**

---

# 🌐 4. Create Repository on GitHub

Go to: https://github.com

Click:
- ➕ → **New repository**

Fill:
- Name: `password-generator-pro`
- Description: `GUI Password Generator with strength checker`
- Public ✅
- Add README ❌ (you already made it)

Click **Create repository**

---

# 🔗 5. Connect Your Project to GitHub

Copy your repo URL, then in Terminal:

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - Password Generator Pro"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/password-generator-pro.git
git push -u origin main
